## 4. TECH STACK — ALWAYS USE, NEVER REPLACE

| Package | Purpose |
|---|---|
| gsap + @gsap/react | All scroll and timeline animations |
| three + @react-three/fiber + @react-three/drei | 3D scenes |
| framer-motion | Component-level motion |
| lenis | Smooth scrolling |
| split-type | Text split for character/word/line reveals |
| anime.js | Icon morphing, number scramble |
| @studio-freight/lenis | Smooth scroll (alias) |
| react-intersection-observer | Lazy-trigger animations |
| react-parallax-tilt | Card hover tilt effect |
| react-countup | Animated stat counters |
| swiper | Carousels and sliders |
| @radix-ui/react-dialog | Accessible modals |

Do not swap any of these for alternatives.

---

## 5. FRAMEWORK RULES

- If the project is **Next.js**: add `"use client"` at the top of EVERY animation component.
- If **Vite/React**: proceed normally, no `"use client"` needed.
- All GSAP plugins must be registered once in `App.jsx` or the top-level entry:
  ```js
  gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger, ScrollSmoother)
  ```
- Lenis must be synced with GSAP ticker:
  ```js
  const lenis = new Lenis({ duration: 1.4, easing: (t) => Math.min(1, 1.001 - Math.pow(2, -10 * t)) })
  lenis.on('scroll', ScrollTrigger.update)
  gsap.ticker.add((time) => { lenis.raf(time * 1000) })
  gsap.ticker.lagSmoothing(0)
  ```

