## 8. RESPONSIVE BREAKPOINTS

```css
/* Mobile  */ @media (max-width: 768px)
/* Tablet  */ @media (min-width: 769px) and (max-width: 1024px)
/* Desktop */ @media (min-width: 1025px)
/* Wide    */ @media (min-width: 1440px)
```

- Section padding: min `80px` top/bottom on mobile, `120px` on desktop.
- All 2-column layouts stack on mobile.

---

## 9. MOBILE & PERFORMANCE RULES

- **Disable Three.js heavy scenes on mobile** — detect touch: `'ontouchstart' in window` — use fallback gradient animation.
- **Disable custom cursor on touch devices**.
- **Reduce particle count** to 500 on mobile (2000 on desktop).
- Three.js renderer: `antialias: false` on mobile, `pixelRatio: Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio, 2)`.
- Use `will-change: transform` ONLY on actively animating elements. Remove it after animation ends.
- Lazy load ALL images with `loading="lazy"`.
- Use `IntersectionObserver` before initializing heavy Three.js scenes.
- Dispose Three.js geometries and materials on component unmount.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`:
  ```js
  const prefersReducedMotion = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches
  if (!prefersReducedMotion) { /* init all GSAP animations */ }
  ```
- Use `gsap.matchMedia()` for responsive animation configurations.
- Lighthouse Performance target: **90+**.

