## 13. CODE QUALITY RULES

- No inline styles unless strictly necessary for dynamic GSAP values.
- All CSS custom properties go in `:root {}`.
- Component files must not exceed ~300 lines — split if needed.
- No `console.log` in production code.
- All Three.js scenes must clean up on unmount (`useEffect` return).
- Use semantic HTML: `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, `<article>`.
- All interactive elements must have accessible `aria-label` attributes.

---

## 14. DO NOT

- Do NOT change brand colors.
- Do NOT use dark backgrounds (the theme is light, airy, premium).
- Do NOT skip Lenis initialization.
- Do NOT forget `"use client"` on animation components in Next.js.
- Do NOT use `localStorage` or `sessionStorage` unless explicitly asked.
- Do NOT hardcode font sizes in `px` — use CSS custom properties or `clamp()`.
- Do NOT remove the scroll progress bar.
- Do NOT skip the preloader.
- Do NOT merge section components into one file.
